I got myself an old school organic buckwheat hulls pillow and have been sleeping on it very well. Firmer than regular pillows, but slowly molds and adapts to your sleeping position with time. As someone here jokingly said, it's the sort of thing that Tom Sawyer would sleep on.

Back at my village my grandmother still has homemade straw-filled pillows from her childhood so I sort of get to experience the full circle back to traditional products in one single lifetime. Only difference is now you have to pay literally a thousand times more for this stuff.

"... We look for our way... In a Sky without Light..."

That video of Justin Bieber singing "Baby" in the abandoned bowling alley with his drug addict body is so hauntingly beautiful. I am sorry I publicly wanted to hurt him on Facebook back in the second grade. Instead now I want to nurture and protect Bieber. We have both grown.

In that time he was a symbol of effeminate behavior and womanizing so we had to oppose his influence. Now in retrospect he's a symbol of the previous American culture and pre-mass digitalization life so we have to romanticize and support him. Dialectic materialism.
